Libalgo - Cryptographic Library
═══════════════════════════════
LibAlgo is an open-source C library offering a comprehensive suite
of low-level implementations of cryptographic algorithms. Distributed
under the GPLv2 licence, it is designed to provide robust, efficient,
and optimised implementations for a variety of cryptographic needs.

LibAlgo includes a well-tested collection of cipher algorithms, hash
functions, and HMAC implementations to meet modern security requirements.


Block ciphers
┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈
  • AES and AES-NI (hardware-accelerated AES)
  • Anubis
  • Blowfish
  • Serpent
  • Twofish

Stream ciphers
┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈
  • ChaCha20 and Salsa20
  • ARCFOUR

Hash Functions
┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈
  • BLAKE2b
  • SHA-1
  • SHA-256 and SHA-512
  • Whirlpool

HMAC Implementations
┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈
  • HMAC-BLAKE2b
  • HMAC-SHA-1
  • HMAC-SHA-256 and HMAC-SHA-512
  • HMAC-Whirlpool

Key Derivation Functions
┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈┈
  • Argon2


